  "instructions": [
    "Heat canola oil in a tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the ground beef and cook until browned, breaking it up into small pieces as it cooks.",
    "Add the tomato paste and red wine, stirring to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro.",
    "Serve hot, with additional canola oil on the side if desired."
